uiFolder.couldNotCopyProblemReportToClipboard: Could not copy problem report to clipboard.
uiFolder.rSessionExitedWithCode: The R session process exited with code {{- exitCode}}.
uiFolder.rCanFailToStartupForManyReasons: R can fail to start up for many reasons. The following may help you resolve the problem:
uiFolder.makeSureThatRStartsUpCorrectly: Make sure that R starts up correctly outside RStudio (using RGui, R.app, or R in a terminal).
uiFolder.fullyUninstallAllVersionsOfRFromYourMach: Fully uninstall all versions of R from your machine, and reinstall the version you wish to use with RStudio.
uiFolder.removeStartupCustomizationsSuchAs: Remove startup customizations such as an {{- rProfileFileExtension}} file, if present.
uiFolder.ifPostingThisReportOnlineUseTheCopyProbl: If posting this report online, use the Copy Problem Report button below to generate a textual version of this diagnostic.
uiFolder.furtherTroubleshootingHelpCanBeFound: Further troubleshooting help can be found on our website:
uiFolder.rstudioCantEstablishAConnectionToR: RStudio can't establish a connection to R. This usually indicates one of the following:
uiFolder.theRSessionIsTakingAnUnusuallyLongTimeTo: The R session is taking an unusually long time to start, perhaps because of slow operations in startup scripts or slow network drive access.
uiFolder.rstudioIsUnableToCommunicateWithR: RStudio is unable to communicate with R over a local network port, possibly because of firewall restrictions or anti-virus software.
uiFolder.ifYouveCustomizedRSessionCreation: If you've customized R session creation by creating an R profile (e.g. located at {{- rProfileFileExtension}} consider temporarily removing it.
uiFolder.ifYouAreUsingAFirewallOrAntivirus: If you are using a firewall or antivirus software which guards access to local network ports, add an exclusion for the RStudio and rsession executables.
uiFolder.runRguiRAppOrRInATerminalToEnsure: Run RGui, R.app, or R in a terminal to ensure that R itself starts up correctly.
uiFolder.theRsessionIsInitializing: The R session is initializing {{- mdash}} please wait a moment...
uiFolder.rSessionFailedToStart: The R session failed to start.

sessionLauncherTs.errorWasCausedByRAttemptingToLoadPackage: This error was very likely caused by R attempting to load packages from a different incompatible version of R on your system. Please remove other versions of R and/or remove environment variables that reference libraries from other versions of R before proceeding.
